    Function reference

    All functions

    detect_os()
    (internal function) Find the operating system of the user
    execute_bin()
    (internal function) Execution of the compiled files
    format_config()
    (internal function) Read the configuration file and format it for the input file.
    format_dataframe_to_txt()
    (internal function) Create the input data file from a dataframe
    format_row()
    (internal function) Format a single row for the input data file
    get_effects()
    (internal function) Get the estimation in the output file
    get_likelihood()
    (internal function) get the likelihood in the output file
    get_param_ranges()
    (internal function) Get the parameter ranges/boundaries in the output file
    get_ratio_max()
    (internal function) Get the ratio max in the output file
    get_seeds()
    (internal function) Get the seeds in the output file

    Main function of the lifelihood program
    parse_output()
    (internal function) Parse results from the output file
    read_output_from_file()
    (internal function) Read and format the output file of the program
    summary(<LifelihoodResults>)
    Custom summary function for lifelihood
    write_param_range()
    (internal function) Write parameter ranges/boundaries to a file
